#Text=Racine County Jane
#Text=Doe
#Text=Racine County Jane
#Text=Doe
#Text=( informally known as Crystal Rae ) [ 2 ] was a young white woman whose body was discovered in 1999 in the town of Raymond , Racine County , Wisconsin . [ 3 ]
#Text=The victim was aged 18 to 35 years at the time of her death , which had occurred after her enduring several weeks of extreme neglect and both physical and sexual abuse . [ 4 ]
#Text=New developments in the case have emerged after her body was exhumed on October 16 , 2013 .
#Text=It is not known how successfully these leads have been followed . [ 5 ]
#Text=Discovery of the body
#Text=Racine County Jane Doe was discovered close to a field on July 21 , 1999 .
#Text=Her death had occurred within one day of the discovery of her body . [ 1 ] [ 6 ] [ 7 ] [ 8 ]
#Text=One of the two people who discovered the body stated that an arm appeared to be broken , since it was in an unnatural position . [ 7 ]
#Text=Because it had rained on the night the body was dumped , little evidence of the perpetrator was found . [ 4 ] [ 5 ]

#Text=An autopsy indicated this young woman had died from a combination of multiple injuries , such as burning and beating , and had endured several weeks of neglect and both physical and sexual abuse , which had increased in severity in the days immediately prior to her death . [ 7 ] [ 9 ]

#Text=She showed signs of having been malnourished and sexually abused . [ 1 ] [ 6 ] A " cauliflower ear " deformity evident upon her body may have been caused by the extensive abuse which she had been forced to endure in the weeks prior to her death . [ 6 ] [ 10 ]

column1: #Text=Over 50 people attended the woman 's funeral after the autopsy was completed . [ 6 ] [ 9 ]
#Text=Her gravestone reads " Daughter : Jane Doe " , along with the relevant dates . [ 1 ] [ 3 ]
#Text=Description
#Text=Additional Facial reconstruction of Racine County Jane Doe
#Text=Racine County Jane Doe may have been a mentally disabled individual .
#Text=She had a " cauliflower ear " deformity , which likely resulted from abuse . [ 1 ] [ 3 ]

column1: #Text=It is believed that she was most likely 18 to 30 years old , although she may have been up to 35 . [ 2 ] [ 11 ]
#Text=Her teeth were not well cared for .
#Text=Her front incisors protruded from the mouth , and decay was present on many teeth .
#Text=Some teeth were missing . [ 3 ] [ 5 ]
#Text=Her curly hair was reddish-brown , collar-length , and appeared to have blond highlights . [ 3 ]
#Text=Her eyes were either brown , green , or hazel .
#Text=There were two earrings in each of her ears . [ 2 ] [ 4 ] [ 7 ]
#Text=She had visible bruises and cuts across her body , and a fractured nose . [ 12 ] [ 13 ]
#Text=She wore a man 's shirt , gray in color , with a floral design on the front .
#Text=After contacting the shirt 's manufacturer , it was learned that this type of shirt was first sold in 1984 . [ 5 ] [ 6 ] [ 8 ]
#Text=She was also wearing black sweatpants .
#Text=She was not wearing shoes . [ 1 ] [ 3 ] [ 4 ]
#Text=Investigation
#Text=Multiple reconstructions have been created of the decedent 's face . [ 4 ]
#Text=In 2012 , an additional reconstruction was created by the National Center for Missing and Exploited Children . [ 14 ]
#Text=Another version of this facial composite exists , which depicts a differing facial rendition of how Racine County Jane Doe may have appeared in life . [ 5 ] [ 7 ]

#Text=At one time , she was thought to be Aundria " Alexis " Bowman , who was presumed to have run away from her adoptive parents ' house in Hamilton , Michigan on March 11 , 1989 , but DNA profiling via her mother Cathy demonstrated that they were not the same person .
#Text=Missing persons such as Aundria , Tina D'Ambrosio , and Karen Wells have been ruled out . [ 1 ] [ 15 ] [ 16 ] [ 17 ]
#Text=Some believed that this case could be linked to the murder of Mary Kate Chamizo ( née : Sunderlin ) , a previously unidentified victim who was discovered in Lake County , Illinois .
#Text=Sunderlin was also found malnourished , had poor dentition and had been beaten to death .
#Text=Three were arrested in that case ; one was convicted . [ 18 ] [ 19 ]
#Text=All three were later cleared due to new evidence . [ 20 ]
#Text=Alternate facial reconstructions of the victim , made prior to the creation of her 2012 facial composite
#Text=The remains were exhumed on October 16 , 2013 , for further study and transported to Milwaukee , Wisconsin , where the body had previously been examined in 1999 . [ 3 ] [ 8 ] [ 21 ]
#Text=Authorities hoped that by studying the bones , they would be able to tell where the woman had lived prior to her death . [ 6 ]
#Text=It was announced on July 19 , 2015 , that the examination of the remains had been completed and that they would be reburied on July 21 on the 16th anniversary of their discovery . [ 22 ]
#Text=Authorities stated they had indeed uncovered new leads from the exhumation , but they declined to state any details . [ 23 ]

#Text=On October 20 , 2016 it was announced that chemical isotope testing performed by the Smithsonian on a sample of her hair and bone suggest she may originally have been from or spent several years of her life in Alaska , Montana or portions of southern Canada .
#Text=Authorities did not comment on what testing the results are from , whether recent with hair or history from bone . [ 24 ]
#Text=Although the murder remains unsolved , investigators hope that the case will eventually come to a close .
#Text=A press conference in 2013 is said to have uncovered more clues . [ 3 ] [ 5 ] [ 25 ]
